This paper is primarily focused on visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using a convolutional neural network to learn to update the appearance template, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves robotics (cs.RO) since visual tracking is an important component of many robotic systems. Finally, the experiments involve evaluating the performance of the proposed method on various datasets, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
